response.original_title: Alicia Keys live North Sea Jazz
response.overview: Alicia Keys holds 14 Grammy Awards and is a world-famous singer, songwriter, producer, actress, New York Times best-selling author, entrepreneur and humanitarian. Keys has built an unparalleled repertoire of hits with more than 30 million albums sold worldwide. As an actress, Keys has featured in Smokin’ Aces’, The Nanny Diaries and The Secret Life of Bees. Keys made her directorial debut in 2011 with Lili, a short film for an anthology of Lifetime’s five short films about breast cancer.  “We are excited to have such an acclaimed artist, Alicia Keys, join our reputable line up of performers,” says Curaçao Tourist Board CEO Ghatim Kabbara. “Travelers from all over the world will be joining us for the concert festival of the year, heightening awareness of Curaçao as the hottest destination for music in the Caribbean.”
